{
  "text": "The cost of medications also plays into the overall cost of treating pediatric patients with CDI. Commercially available oral vancomycin costs ~US$71-US$143/d (depending on the dosing regimen chosen) compared to only US$2/d with oral metronidazole. [CITATION_1] 51 Even though oral vancomycin can be compounded extemporaneously, which can reduce cost, there is still a significant price difference compared to metronidazole, which can affect compliance. [CITATION_2] Oral fidaxomicin costs ~US$335/d, which makes it the most expensive currently available CDI treatment. 51 However, economic calculations often include additional factors besides the cost of the drug treatment when assessing the cost-effectiveness of a medication.",
